## Restrictions

### DO NOT
- Hardcode secrets, API keys, or credentials
- Commit `.env` files or secret values
- Modify shared library chart without understanding all consumers
- Skip health checks in service configurations
- Use `latest` tag in production Helm values
- Disable security contexts or run containers as root
- Add dependencies without checking license compatibility
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- Use `any` type in TypeScript (use `unknown` + type narrowing)
- Import from `dist/` paths directly (use package name){{ end }}
{{ if hasItem .Project.Spec.Infrastructure.Components "hasura" }}- Modify Hasura migrations in production directly (use migration files){{ end }}

### ALWAYS
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Include health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)
- Add resource requests/limits to Helm values
- Write tests for new functionality
- Follow the existing patterns in the codebase
- Use the shared library chart for new services
